    "Trace has 0 errors — the test passes; the validation message is the asserted expected behaviour, not a failure.",
    "Two browser contexts: trader (/notification/vnet/protected/...) creates and submits, inspector (/decision/vnet/protected/...) then acts on the same CHED. Actions 91-92 are the role switch (new context + page).",
    "Allowed attachment types per the error copy: DOC, JPEG, PDF, PNG, XLS. ZIP is rejected. The trader-side upload at action 65 used example.png and was accepted — the same upload surface, so this is one shared file-type rule exercised from two roles.",
    "The inspector upload flow mirrors the trader one: Document type + Document reference + issue date (Day/Month/Year) then 'Add attachment' -> file input -> 'Next'. Only the Document type option set differs ('Phytosanitary certificate' trader-side, 'Other' inspector-side).",
    "ARCHITECTURE FINDING: attachment upload is a SEPARATE service (/upload/...) from both the notification and decision services, reached by a cross-service hop and keyed by reference id + index + originating-context segment (DRAFT.GB.../0/notification vs CHEDPP.GB.../0/decision). The new CDP app need not reproduce this split.",
